The loser's corpse will appear at their bind point with all their items intact.<br>
Basically, Manaburn will be a tool for removing players from a zone.<br>
<br>
2. Looting rules will be changed so that if your character  can't use an item (Race/Class), you can't loot it. Coin loot will remain unchanged.<br>
<br>
3. On top of the 66% spell damage reduction in PvP, will be level based spell damage reductions when attacking lower level players. <br>
<br>
Example:<br>
Target is your level: You % damage remains unchanged<br>
Target is -1 levels bellow you: You lose 5% damage<br>
Target is -2 levels bellow you: You lose 10% damage<br>
Target is -3 levels bellow you: You lose 20% damage<br>
Target is -4 levels bellow you: You lose 30% damage<br>
<br>
4. Resistance &quot;debuff&quot; spells (currently set at 150% functionality) will scale depending on difference in levels between your character and your target.<br>
<br>
Example:<br>
Target is +4 levels above you: You gain 40% to debuff effects<br>
Target is +3 levels above you: You gain 20% to debuff effects<br>
Target is +2 levels above you: You gain 10% to debuff effects<br>
Target is +1 levels above you: You gain 5% to debuff effects<br>
Target is your level: You gain 0% to debuff effects<br>
<br>
5. City Zones will be Non-PvP areas, excluding Greater Faydark, The Overthere, and Fironia Vie. Arenas in city zones will remain PvP areas.<br>
<br>
6. Victors in PvP will have a PvP faction hit with the loser, and /consider will reflect it. If a players faction with another player drops bellow dubious, they will not be able to group together. Duels are excluded from PvP faction hits, as are victories in arenas.<br>
These faction hits are strictly for PvP, and have no bearing on PvE factions. Players can forgive (reset another players PvP faction with themself) by using the /forgive command.<br>
<br>
7. Victors in PvP will have a PvP faction hit with the losers guild (if the loser belongs to a guild), and /consider will reflect it.<br>
If a players faction with a guild drops bellow dubious, they will not be able to group with any member of the losers guild, or join the guild unless invited by the Guild Leader. Duels are excluded from PvP faction hits, as are victories in arenas.<br>
These faction hits are strictly for PvP, and have no bearing on PvE factions. Guild leaders have the ability to pardon (reset a guild members PvP faction with their guild) by using the /pardon command.<br>
<br>
8. Joining a group renders you PvP immune to attacks from fellow group members unless you're dueling or in an arena.<br>
<br>
9. Joining a guild renders you PvP immune to attacks from fellow guild members unless you're dueling or in an arena.<br>
<br>
10. Joining a raid group renders you PvP immune to attacks from fellow raid members unless you're dueling or in an arena. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jarnin>Jarnin</A> at: 1/28/03 3:12:38 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=agozrz>agozrz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/24/03 11:55 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:</span><hr size=1> I just skimmed it...<br>
