<br>
The point of PvP faction hits is so that you know who has attacked you or your guild (if you belong to one) by /consider.<br>
Each time a person attacks and kills you, they get a PvP faction hit with you, which would lower your &quot;opinion&quot; of them.<br>
<br>
Example:<br>
<br>
Joe the wizard kills Bob the warrior. Joe takes a faction hit with Bob, and from that point on, if Bob considers Joe, he will see that he's been attacked by him before (his consider message would go from being indifferent or &quot;neutral&quot; to apprehensive).<br>
If Joe kills Bob a few more times, Joes faction will drop so far down that he can no longer group with Bob (players can no longer group together after they hit threatening status).<br>
<br>
If Bob belongs to a guild, Joe will take PvP faction hits with Bob's guild as well. After Joes faction drops to threatening with Bob's guild, Joe will no longer be able to group with any member of Bob's guild.<br>
<br>
Now, in the event that Joe makes amends with Bob, Bob can forgive Joe, which resets his faction with Bob, allowing them to group. However, Joe would still not be able to group with Bob's guildmates unless the guild leader of Bob's guild pardons Joe.<br>
<br>
The reason I came up with this rule is to deal with random PKs. I know of many players that will randomly kill players, and then a few weeks later they want to group with them, or members their guild. So, in order to give players a little more control over these situations, the random PKs are penalized. This prevents them from getting away with randomly killing players, and then hanging out with a victims friends.<br>
<br>
As for those PvP immunities regarding groups, guilds and raids, what downsides do you see? <br>
I really can't see any problems besides the fun of smacking your friends around during downtimes, but that's not really a downside. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=velaelsoulrender>Velael Soulrender</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>The Snuggly SZ'r!</span><br>  Posts: 1034<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/25/03 12:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 10 suggested changes for Rallos Zek PvP rules</span><hr size=1> If you didn't have the spell damage nerf for PvP, PoP lures would be absolutely unreal (as opposed to just a bit overpowered now). With focus effects, and the resist changes, there is 0 reason to lift the damage nerf. Wizards are fucking gods on 2 legs already in pvp. <p>Retired Arcanist of <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.hateguild.org">Hate</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
